The paper focuses on analyzing user engagement with video content on YouTube, which involves aspects of social media, multimedia, human-computer interaction, information retrieval, and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
